A minimum of 10 percent, but not more than 40 percent, of the course of fire rounds shall be discharged at each of the following four range of distances:
(a) Less than 5 yards;
(b) 5 yards to less than 10 yards;
(c) 10 to less than 25 yards; and
(d) 25 yards or farther.

(a) 2 seconds per round when firing at less than 5 yards;
(b) 3 seconds per round when firing at 5 yards to less than 10 yards;
(c) 4 seconds per round when firing at 10 yards to less than 25 yards;
(d) 5 seconds per round when firing at 25 yards, or farther

(a) 2 seconds per round when firing at less than 5 yards;
